```

### Coverage status

```
grep -n "header_validator_\|transformResponseHeaders\|new_headers" \
  test/common/http/conn_manager_impl_test*.cc
# No test configures a header_validator_ that returns non-null new_headers.
```

The test harness (`HttpConnectionManagerImplTest`) leaves `header_validator_`
null in every test. Even in tests that do configure a validator, the mock returns
a result with `new_headers == nullptr`. The `else if (result.new_headers)` branch
at line 2020–2022 is therefore never taken: `response_encoder_->encodeHeaders`
is called with the replacement map exactly zero times in the unit test suite.

### Proposed test

```cpp
TEST_F(HttpConnectionManagerImplTest, EncodeHeadersWithHeaderValidatorTransform) {
  // Install a mock header validator that rewrites response headers
  auto* mock_validator = new NiceMock<MockHeaderValidator>();
  EXPECT_CALL(*mock_validator, transformResponseHeaders(_))
      .WillOnce(Invoke([](ResponseHeaderMap& headers)
                           -> Http::HeaderValidator::TransformationResult {
        auto new_hdrs = ResponseHeaderMapImpl::create();
        new_hdrs->setStatus(200);
        new_hdrs->addCopy(LowerCaseString("x-transformed"), "yes");
        return {Http::HeaderValidator::RejectOrRedirectResponse::Accept,
                std::move(new_hdrs)};
      }));
  header_validator_ = std::unique_ptr<HeaderValidator>(mock_validator);
  setup();
  setupFilterChain(1, 0);

  EXPECT_CALL(*decoder_filters_[0], decodeHeaders(_, true))
      .WillOnce(Return(FilterHeadersStatus::StopIteration));
  startRequest(true);

  // encodeHeaders must be called with the REPLACEMENT map, not the original
  EXPECT_CALL(response_encoder_, encodeHeaders(_, true))
      .WillOnce(Invoke([](const ResponseHeaderMap& headers, bool) {
        // Validate the replacement header is present
        EXPECT_EQ("yes", headers.get(LowerCaseString("x-transformed"))[0]
                             ->value().getStringView());
      }));
  expectOnDestroy();

  ResponseHeaderMapPtr response_headers{
      new TestResponseHeaderMapImpl{{":status", "200"}}};
  decoder_filters_[0]->callbacks_->streamInfo().setResponseCodeDetails("");
  decoder_filters_[0]->callbacks_->encodeHeaders(std::move(response_headers), true, "details");
}
```

### Risk

**High.** The header-validator transform is the mechanism by which Envoy enforces
HTTP/1 or HTTP/2 protocol compliance (e.g., removing invalid pseudo-headers,
normalising field names for RFC 9110 conformance). If the `new_headers` swap
branch is silently broken, Envoy would send the un-validated original headers
downstream, bypassing all validator transformations. This is a potential security
and interoperability regression.

