## Summary Table

| # | File | Function / Branch | Key Lines | Risk | Test Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `conn_manager_impl.cc` | `isPrematureRstStream` + `maybeDrainDueToPrematureResets` | 677–698, 702–748 | 🔴 High | No unit tests; integration-only |
| 2 | `conn_manager_impl.cc` | `sendGoAwayAndClose(false)` non-graceful path + `go_away_sent_` guard | 797–823 | 🟠 Medium-High | Only `graceful=true` tested |
| 3 | `conn_manager_impl.cc` | HTTP/1.0 `Connection: keep-alive` header emission | 1938–1948 | 🟡 Medium | All HTTP/1.0 tests drain/close |
| 4 | `conn_manager_impl.cc` | `chargeStats` InternalRedirect skip | 1078–1084 | 🟡 Medium | No test sets InternalRedirect detail |
| 5 | `conn_manager_impl.cc` | `encodeHeaders` header-validator `new_headers` swap | 2014–2023 | 🔴 High | All test validators return null `new_headers` |
| 6 | `filter_manager.cc` | `addDecodedData`/`addEncodedData` `IS_ENVOY_BUG` + 502 | 824–828, 1429–1433 | 🟠 Medium-High | Never triggered |
| 7 | `filter_manager.cc` | `checkAndCloseStreamIfFullyClosed` error-response abort | 1572–1584 | 🔴 High | All half-close tests use 200 OK |
| 8 | `header_map_impl.cc` | `maybeMakeMap` lazy-map build + `getExisting` lazy-map lookup | 56–68, 347–374 | 🟡 Medium | All tests use ≤2 non-inline headers |

**Legend:** 🔴 High — security or correctness regression likely to be invisible in staging
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;🟠 Medium-High — incorrect behaviour under specific but reachable conditions
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;🟡 Medium — performance or observability regression; no immediate safety impact

---

## How to Prioritise Remediation

1. **Gap 7** (half-close error branch) and **Gap 5** (header-validator swap) first —
   both are one-line conditions that route encoding to the wrong code path;
   regression is silent and can affect every request.

2. **Gap 1** (premature-RST drain) second — security-relevant; the absence of unit
   tests means any refactor to `doDeferredStreamDestroy` could silently break the
   flood-defence mechanism.

3. **Gap 6** (`IS_ENVOY_BUG` 502) third — validates a defensive contract that
   third-party filter authors rely on; straightforward to add.

4. **Gaps 2, 3, 4** — important correctness gaps with moderate blast radius;
   feasible to close in a single test PR.

5. **Gap 8** (lazy map) — performance optimisation; low urgency but worth
   including as part of a `header_map_impl` test hardening pass.

