# Envoy HTTP Connection Manager — Test Coverage Gap Analysis

## Scope

This document analyses test coverage gaps across three core Envoy HTTP source files
and their corresponding unit-test suites:

| Source file | Lines | Primary test file(s) | Test cases |
|---|---|---|---|
| `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc` | 2,607 | `conn_manager_impl_test.cc` (5,407 ln) <br> `conn_manager_impl_test_2.cc` (2,271 ln) <br> `conn_manager_impl_test_3.cc` (2,903 ln) | ~223 |
| `source/common/http/filter_manager.cc` | 1,989 | `filter_manager_test.cc` | ~60 |
| `source/common/http/header_map_impl.cc` | 542 | `header_map_impl_test.cc` (1,091 ln) | 36 |

Analysis method: systematic cross-referencing of every non-trivial branch in the
three source files against the full body of unit tests, followed by targeted `grep`
searches to rule out incidental coverage.

---

## Gap 1 — Premature-RST detection and connection drain (`conn_manager_impl.cc:677–748`)

### Code under scrutiny

```cpp
// conn_manager_impl.cc:677-698
bool ConnectionManagerImpl::isPrematureRstStream(const ActiveStream& stream) const {
  absl::optional<std::chrono::nanoseconds> duration =
      stream.filter_manager_.streamInfo().currentDuration();
  if (duration) {
    const uint64_t lifetime =
        std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::seconds>(*duration).count();
    const uint64_t min_lifetime = runtime_.snapshot().getInteger(
        ConnectionManagerImpl::PrematureResetMinStreamLifetimeSecondsKey, 1);
    if (lifetime > min_lifetime) {
      return false;          // ← branch A: long-lived stream, NOT premature
    }
  }
  return !stream.filter_manager_.streamInfo().responseCode();  // ← branch B / C
}

// conn_manager_impl.cc:702-748
void ConnectionManagerImpl::maybeDrainDueToPrematureResets() {
  if (drained_due_to_premature_resets_) { return; }   // ← guard: never tested
  if (closed_non_internally_destroyed_requests_ == 0) { return; }

  const uint64_t limit = runtime_.snapshot().getInteger(
      ConnectionManagerImpl::PrematureResetTotalStreamCountKey, 500);

  if (closed_non_internally_destroyed_requests_ < limit) {
    if (number_premature_stream_resets_ * 2 < limit) { return; } // ← ratio branch
  } else {
    if (number_premature_stream_resets_ * 2 <              // ← limit-exceeded branch
        closed_non_internally_destroyed_requests_) { return; }
  }

  if (read_callbacks_->connection().state() == Network::Connection::State::Open) {
    stats_.named_.downstream_rq_too_many_premature_resets_.inc();
    drained_due_to_premature_resets_ = true;
    doConnectionClose(Network::ConnectionCloseType::Abort, absl::nullopt,
                      "too_many_premature_resets");    // ← drain action: never tested
  }
}
```

### Coverage status

`grep -rn "isPrematureRstStream\|maybeDrainDueToPrematureResets\|premature_reset\|PrematureReset"` across
`test/common/http/conn_manager_impl_test*.cc` returns **zero hits**. Both functions
are called from `doDeferredStreamDestroy` (line 324) and `onResetStream` (line 391)
respectively but no unit test drives that call chain into either function body.
Coverage exists only in integration tests (`multiplexed_integration_test.cc`), which
do not exercise individual branches in isolation.

### Untested branches

| Branch | Location | Risk |
|---|---|---|
| `lifetime > min_lifetime` → returns `false` | :689–691 | Incorrect return value means good streams counted as bad |
| `responseCode()` present → returns `false` | :697 | Completed streams misclassified |
| `drained_due_to_premature_resets_` recursion guard | :716–718 | Stack-overflow protection unverified |
